<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Columbus Climate</h2>
<p>For Columbus's hot-humid climate, high-efficiency heat pump systems with SEER ratings of 18+ offer the best year-round performance. These systems excel at both cooling during the extended summer season and providing efficient heating during mild winters when temperatures rarely drop below freezing. Variable-speed compressors are particularly beneficial as they can adjust output to match demand, providing better humidity control and more consistent temperatures. Two-stage systems also work well, offering high capacity during peak summer heat while operating efficiently during milder conditions. Given that cooling represents about 75% of annual HVAC usage in Columbus, prioritizing high cooling efficiency over heating performance typically provides the best return on investment. Systems should include enhanced dehumidification features and be sized properly - oversized units will short-cycle and fail to adequately remove humidity, while undersized systems will struggle during peak summer conditions.</p>

